A member of staff draws the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine out of a phial at the Southmead Hospital, Briston. JOHANNESBURG - Namibia is gearing itself up to receive the much anticipated COVID-19 vaccine. It has appointed a technical team to look into the logistical requirements of importing the vaccine. READ: What we know about Covid-19 vaccines and side effects Most vaccine candidates so far need to be stored in very cold conditions. This makes it difficult for many countries on the continent, that lack the infrastructure needed. Meanwhile, Egypt took delivery of its first batch of the vaccine last week.